components.name: Load and Modify Data
components.description: Ingests CSV files from the configured data directory and converts them to JSON format for pipeline processing using the loadandmodify service. Uses the default image entrypoint.

connections.purpose: Mounted data directory shared across containers

components.name: Data Reconciliation
components.description: Standardizes city names in the JSON files using the HERE geocoding service. Uses the default image entrypoint.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after Load and Modify Data succeeds

connections.purpose: Mounted data directory shared across containers

components.name: OpenMeteo Data Extension
components.description: Enriches the reconciled JSON data with weather attributes from the OpenMeteo service. Uses the default image entrypoint.

connections.purpose: Mounted data directory shared across containers

components.name: Column Extension
components.description: Appends additional data properties (e.g., id, name) to the OpenMeteoenriched JSON files as defined by integration parameters. Uses the default image entrypoint.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after OpenMeteo Data Extension succeeds

connections.purpose: Mounted data directory shared across containers

components.name: Save Final Data
components.description: Consolidates the columnextended JSON files and exports the fully enriched dataset as a CSV file. Uses the default image entrypoint.

connections.purpose: Mounted data directory shared across containers

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

dataset_id.description: Identifier of the dataset to process

date_column_name.description: Name of the column containing date values

table_naming_convention.description: Pattern used to name output tables (e.g., 'JOT_{}')

data_dir.description: Directory containing input CSV files (mounted via environment variable)

optional_columns.description: Additional columns that may be used for reconciliation

reconciliator_id.description: Identifier of the reconciliator to use

date_separator.description: Separator character used when formatting dates for the OpenMeteo service

extender_id.description: Identifier of the column extender to apply

output_dir.description: Directory where the final enriched CSV file will be stored

DATA_DIR.description: Path to the shared data directory mounted into Docker containers

HERE_API_TOKEN.description: API token required for the HERE geocoding service

sources: Raw CSV files located in the shared data directory (/app/data)
HERE Geocoding service accessed via the reconciliation API
OpenMeteo weather service accessed via its public API
sinks: Final enriched CSV file (enriched_data_{}.csv) written to the shared data directory (/app/data)
